'''''Regarding Henry''''' is a film by [[Mike Nichols]] starring [[Harrison Ford]] and [[Annette Bening]].

==Plot==
{{spoiler}}
Ford plays a successful [[lawyer]] who has little time for his wife or daughter, until one night when he receives gunshot wounds to the head and chest, resulting in [[brain damage]]. Henry survives, but he initially cannot move or talk or remember anyone or anything. He regains movement and speech with help from Bradley, his [[physical therapy|physical therapist]]. Henry returns home and discovers that he did not like the person he was before. He forges a new relationship with his wife and daughter and they are all the more happy for it.

==Reception==
Annette Bening won the newcomer of the year [[London Film Critics Circle]] award<ref>{{cite web|url=http://criticscircle.org.uk/critics_circle/film_in.asp|title=International newcomer of the year|publisher=London Film Critics Circle|accessdate=2006-03-19}}</ref>; and the film was nominated for two [[Young Artist Awards]]: best family motion picture - drama, and best young actress starring in a motion picture for Mikki Allen.

